who spent three decades working in telecom

00:00:43.290 --> 00:00:47.989
on both the business side and law and policy
side. In November of 2013, he was appointed

00:00:47.989 --> 00:00:54.240
by President Obama to the position of FCC
chairman, where he was unanimously confirmed.

00:00:54.240 --> 00:01:00.920
His tenure as FCC chair was one of the extraordinary
accomplishments on a wide range of issues,

00:01:00.920 --> 00:01:04.850
and it's particularly well-known for ushering
in the FCC's final rule on net neutrality

00:01:04.850 --> 00:01:10.000
in April 2015, which I'm sure is one of many
things that Susan and Chairman Wheeler will

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.780
talk about.
Without further ado, I'm going to turn things

00:01:12.780 --> 00:01:17.830
over to Prof. Crawford and FCC Chairman Tom
Wheeler. Thanks so much.

